  "texts": [
    "For instance, machine learning algorithms have been effectively utilized for non-invasive diagnosis of diseases by analyzing human waste odors.",
    "Techniques like field asymmetric ion mobility spectrometry (FAIMS) and gas chromatography ion mobility spectrometry (GC-IMS) successfully distinguished between pancreatic cancer, colorectal cancer, and inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) and healthy controls.",
    "The analysis demonstrated high accuracy and highlighted the potential for odor profiling in disease monitoring (Wicaksono 2021).",
    "Traditional methods such as support vector machines (SVMs), k-nearest neighbors (kNN), random forests (RFs), and principal component analysis (PCA) have been widely employed, particularly in smaller datasets and resource-constrained environments (Aly 2021; Zhu et al. 2024).",
    "In these scenarios, traditional algorithms typically rely on handcrafted features derived from domain knowledge, employing statistical descriptors or spectral characteristics to facilitate classification."
  ],
